109—Saxa—aras. The order is scara qqae mediis in fluctibus (exstantia) Itali vocant Aras : “ rocks which (standing out) in the midst of the billows the Italians call Altars.” The saxa referred to are probably the rocks just outside the bay of Karthage. Of these, the insula Aeglmurz' is the chief. Some say the Karthaginian priests used to offer sacrifices there to avert shipwrecks on the rocks, hence the term Ara. Others say the Skerkz' rocks are alluded to, situated in

the shallow between Tunis and Sicily.
